
[1]coccolite

   COCCOLITE, n. A variety of augite or pyroxene; called by Hauy,
   granuliform pyroxene. Its color is usually some shade of green. It is
   composed of granular distinct concretions, easily separable, some of
   which present the appearance of crystals whose angles and edges have
   been obliterated.

   Cocculus Indicus, the fruit of the Menispermum cocculus, a poisonous
   berry, often used in adulterating malt liquors.
